ğŸ‘‰ Best possible solution

â“ INTERVIEWER CAN ASK
ğŸ”¥ Q1: Why k % n?

ğŸ‘‰ Because rotating n times gives same array

ğŸ”¥ Q2: Left rotation?

ğŸ‘‰ Left rotate by k = Right rotate by n-k

ğŸ”¥ Q3: Without extra space?

ğŸ‘‰ Yes, reverse method does it in-place

ğŸ”¥ Q4: Can we use extra array?

ğŸ‘‰ Yes, but SC becomes O(n)

ğŸ”¥ Q5: Difference between rotate & shift?

ğŸ‘‰ Rotate keeps all elements, shift loses data

ğŸ”¥ Q6: Edge cases?

k = 0

k > n

n = 1

ğŸ§  ONE-LINE SUMMARY (YAAD KAR)

â€œReverse the array thrice to rotate efficiently.â€
